The #Tokyo2020 #Olympics are in full swing, with athletes from across the world competing for gold. But - with our planet in danger - what could the #Olympics of the future look like? 👇

Nature loss and the climate crisis not only devastate our home - the impacts will be felt (and are already being felt) by us, no matter where we are in the world. 

This means all areas of our lives, including sport, are at risk 😓 #NoNatureNoSport

So, what can we do? We may not all be world-class athletes, but we can all become champions for nature. And we can start today 🏆 

Tap the link in our bio to see what the future olympics could look like, and learn what we can do to avoid it! #StrongerTogether

⚠️Over 2.25 billion tonnes of food is wasted globally⚠️

New research from WWF sheds new light on the scale of our waste and outlines how we need action from farm to fork.

The @unfoodsystems Food Systems Summit is an opportunity to address this issue and develop solutions for on-farm food loss. 

Share this post to your stories to raise awareness. 

#FoodWaste #IntensiveFarming #ClimateChange #GlobalWarming #ClimateCrisis #ClimateAction #SaveThePlanet  #NoPlanetB #ClimateChangeIsReal #ClimateStrike #ClimateEmergency #ClimateJustice #FridaysForFuture #SustainableFarming

How would the legendary @usainbolt fare in a race against a cheetah? And how does iconic competitor @m_phelps00 match up to one of the ocean’s fastest swimmers? 🤔

With the #Tokyo2020 #Olympics just around the corner, we’re looking at athletes of the animal kingdom who’d give the most skilled and talented Olympians a run for their money. We think the last one may surprise you… 🐜

Want to learn more about nature’s greatest athletes? Tap the link in our bio! 🌍

#StrongerTogether #Wildlife #WWF #NatureLovers #NaturePositive

Today is #WorldEmojiDay and we are continuing our celebration with more fun facts! This time about rainforests. 

#DYK The Amazon Rainforest is incredibly diverse

🐜One tree in the Amazon Rainforest is home to more types of ants than some countries 
🐒Across the globe, the Amazon has the highest number of primate species
🌳If we act today, we can secure a future with thriving rainforests.

Be a voice for our incredible rainforests by sharing this post to your story.

#Conservation #WWF #Biodiversity #Wildlife #Rainforest #AmazonRainforest

Tomorrow is #WorldEmojiDay, let’s remind ourselves the ocean is so important to the health of both people and the planet 🌊

💪Our ocean is a planetary super power 
😮‍💨It produces half of the oxygen we breathe
🌎To secure a future where nature and people thrive, we must urgently take action now to restore the health of our ocean 

🙏#TogetherWeCan do even more to protect our ocean and create a sustainable future for people and wildlife.

Share this post to your stories to spread this important message on #WorldEmojiDay

#Conservation #WWF #Biodiversity #Wildlife #Ocean

node.text:
🦈We ALL ❤️ sharks and rays roaming freely around our oceans. Sadly, new WWF analysis reveals how many also travel far and wide when dead because of a global meat trade crossing 200+ borders, for a total value of US$2.6 billion. This makes it an even larger trade than shark fins. 
 
The demand for shark and ray meat globally is fuelling the overfishing 🎣 of these animals and leading to population declines 📉 around the world. Today, 36% of all shark and ray species are at risk of extinction. 
 
Share to your stories to help raise awareness.
 
#SharkAwarenessDay @wwf_med

How would you react to an elephant in your street or a leopard in your garden?🐆🐘

Increased competition over space and resources brings wildlife and people in closer contact. 

Livestock can become prey for predators like leopards, while crops can be damaged by herbivores such as elephants, often resulting in defensive or retaliatory actions by farmers. 

⚠️Conflict between people and animals is one of the main threats to the continued survival of many species in different parts of the world⚠️

A new report explains the complex nature of this problem, its impacts and how to address it so that people and animals can coexist. 

Addressing human-wildlife conflict effectively can create opportunities and benefits for:

🌱Biodiversity
🧑‍🤝‍🧑Communities
🚜Sustainable development
🌍The global economy

Share this post to your stories and help raise greater awareness. 

#wildlife #HabitatLoss #elephants #leopards #HumanWildlifeConflict #NatureLovers #WildlifeLovers

Today, the EU has put in force a ban on 10 single use plastic items! These include cotton bud sticks, cutlery, plates, and straws.

This is a great first step – but we need leaders to do more to protect our oceans and rivers👇
 
Over 8 MILLION tonnes of plastic are discarded into our oceans every year, polluting our oceans and choking wildlife. We need to step up for nature before it’s too late⏰
 
All governments must adopt a global treaty on marine plastic pollution – tap the link in our bio to call on leaders to #StopPlasticPollution today!
